cs.CR, cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SI

The paper deals with privacy-preserving speech transcription, which is a topic related to security and privacy (cs.CR). It also involves machine learning and natural language processing (cs.CL), as well as statistical learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper proposes a new system that lies at an intermediate point in the privacy-utility spectrum, which could be seen as a form of data anonymization or differential privacy (cs.SD).
